record_data.record_plain_text: LWP LESSEE, LLC RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1 Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service LWP Lessee, LLC ("LWP") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Lakefield generating facility ("Lakefield Facility"). The Lakefield Facility is a wind turbine generating facility located in Jackson County, Minnesota near the city of Lakefield, Minnesota. The Lakefield Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by ITC Midwest LLC and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO"). This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth LWP's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Lakefield Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. LWP's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to LWP shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission, Energy and Operating Reserve Markets Tariff. MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $897,587.94. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $897,587.94/12 = $74,798.99.
